<TD>
<IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/icons/icon1.gif" BORDER="0" ALIGN="ABSCENTER">
<FONT SIZE="1" color="#000000" face="Verdana, Arial">
posted November 08, 2000 07:48 PM &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
    &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=edit_post&f=28&t=000061&reply_num=000000&u="><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/edit_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete Post"></A> &nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=reply&f=28&t=000061&replyto=000000"><IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/quote_ubb6.gif" BORDER="0" ALT="Reply With Quote"></A>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
  <BR>   No, I'm not looking for another class envy thread or flamefest.  I have a mage (level 29), and I often see remarks that mages are "good soloers".  I don't get why.  I have an alternate character, 24 druid, and it's clear to me why that's a good solo class.  But with my mage, all I can do is beat up blues, usually win, occasionally die, and then med back up.  That, to me, doesn't qualify as being especially good at solo; more like barely ekeing it out.<P>   Mages lack some very key solo tools, in particular any sort of lull / harmony.  Once you're into even double-digit levels, a great many creatures come in linked groups, and being able to break camps is pretty important.  (Faerie guards in LFay, for example.  The strat guide here that claims you can pull those has gotten me killed twice and run into MM a number of other times.)  Fear is also very useful, to reduce downtime, stagger multiples, and allow battling much tougher creatures.  Lots of other utility spells are missing, of course, in particular any sort of useful healing or mana regen, but those aren't quite as vital.<P>   So, this being the Strategy and Tactics board -- what Strategies and Tactics am I missing out on?  I can generally still beat up blues, only occasionally losing a pet if it's a lucky high blue or a weak elemental, but I don't see how people can solo yellows, as they claim.  Maybe it's just a gimmick, like kiting around your fire pet for a long time.  (No Jboots.)  Maybe chain casting is a lot more powerful than I thought.  (I've pulled up extra pets in combat, but only as a rare desperation measure.  It's slow and risky, but more so solo, I would think.)  But letting the pets do all the work cuts the xp in half right off the top; that doesn't seem like a promising path, unless /pet get lost also wipes the damage done record.   And even with the impressive damage output of a mage and pet, the straightforward approach of just whacking things doesn't seem particularly effective -- at least not enough to make mages one of the supposed top three solo classes.<P>  So what am I missing?<BR>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
