</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I think the yellow soloing thing is probably at the first level you get your new pet and least likely the level before you get your new spells. <P>Find a place with lots of low blues and lay the smack down on them. Wasting all your mana on whites and yellows creates way too much down time. killing two of those blues would give you the same exp and youd still be ready to keep pulling. The key is to find a place with lots to pull.<P>Only if no low blues are available should you bother with the others, and then you might as well blast to get all the exp and med because critters are few and far between.<P>Make sure you use all your talents, burnouts, Pet Heal, Fire Shields. If its fairly high level I use a fire shield for sure and usually my water pet for high damage and regen. <P>If its the final level before you get your new spells, use the Earth pet. At these levels your pet is much lower than the monster so the extra agil and ac means nothing. The monster slices through this like butter and hits anyways. If your pet is gonna get hit anyways, then use Earth cuz hes got more hitpoints.<P>Oh yea, and I always use the pull onto pet trick, it really does help the aggro against you when you blast alot.. just keep your distance and you should be fine. <P>If your quick with your keys you can pet report health, heal pet and then blast, alternating these can be devastating to the mob if your quick enough.<P>Cheer up, its sure to get harder from here 8)<P>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
