<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I've never had any problem soloing, it's just a matter of finding a good spot.  For instance, right now I am 35 and soloing the Yetis in one of the ice caves in the dreadlands.  In back of the cave there is a room with 3 spawns.  They are mostly high blue, with a few evens, and they have a very low aggro factor.<P>Summon Pet<BR>Give Pet 2 Rune Swords<BR>Meditate to full mana<BR>Burnout Pet<BR>Damage Shield Pet<BR>Send Pet to attack Yeti<BR>Immediately cast Malise<BR>Move to a clear line of sight<BR>Cast Cinder Bolt<BR>Cast Cinder Bolt<BR>Cast Cinder Bolt<BR>Loot Yeti corpse<BR>Meditate and wait for next Yeti to pop<BR>Repeat<P>Granted, it's a little boring, and I'd much rather group, but this is helping me get through this hell level much faster.<P>Shiri<BR>
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
