   <BR>   Thanks for the all the tips.  My battles generally go much as Shiri described.<P>   So you'd agree it's mostly just a matter of finding a favorable spot (lone blue with respawn about the same as your med time)?  The druid, in contrast, can fight pretty much anywhere.  And I've assumed just about any class can walk up to a single blue and kill it.  (Perhaps I'm naive there  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif">  I was thinking perhaps there was some special way to reduce downtime or take higher-level target with a mage, given all the talk about what good solo classes they were.  But then, maybe that's just class envy in reverse -- or maybe just being able to kill one blue is a noteworthy thing after all.<BR>
