<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Chain casting is really better at later levels. The monsters are extremely differant from one to the next. An example would easily be a caster versus melee. It really depends on what you get and attack. Remember a caster doesn't want to get hit period,one reason for the preferance for earth pets for soloists. I have even had my pet die but root stick until I could call up another, on good days when the random generator smiles on me.<BR> I've also found crag forest giants to con blue yet kill me without a thought. One example of my experience has been the giants in frontier moutains. The hole to the dreadlands served me well at mid thirties. At first one hillock and down to med back up. As I went up to the mid 30's the hillock could be killed twice and then med back up but the tumps were death yet still blue. After awhile the tumps were two at a time and the brea in the southwest corner were death and blue. At this time the brae are two till med and the crags are death dealers again blue. I am now 41 and spend my time at the burnings woods zone, 'Sorta the zone is to far away for emergency run away.' The shades of blue are obviously the diferrance. <BR>   The mage is great to solo. Just remember to take one at a time and "DON'T GET HIT'. Hope this helps and isn't too confusing. Look to the guides for suggestions of where to hunt and enjoy!
</FONT>
