<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<BR>   How about some tips on the fine points of chain casting?  The strategy guide section explains the general tactic well enough, but what do my fellow mages think about questions like these:<P>   Fire pet or earth pet with damage shield?  Earth is going to cost more mana, but last longer to do more damage.  OTOH, the fire pet has a more powerful shield to start with, for no extra mana.  Your exact level obviously affects the tradeoff here.<P>   Burnout or not?  Is the extra attack benefit worth the extra mana, or should we just save it to add another pet to the chain?<P>   Equipment seems a moot point (even if the swords hadn't been nerfed) because you probably don't have time to give them to the pet.  Still, you do have the opportunity to store them up ahead of the battle, for effectively no mana cost during, if you can get them to the pet without being clobbered.  Does anyone try to equip chained pets?<BR>
</FONT>
