<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Ah the soloing mage... yes we can solo pretty much anything, but there are things we shd solo and things we shd just leave to the necros and druids... we are the masters of fighting npc casters of all types... long time battles by necros or druids fail against these because they cant handle being blasted while they try to kite.  on the flipside they excel at puretank battles like guards or HGs where the mob just hits and hits hard.  In this second case we can solo using hte flameshielded earth pet, which regens fairly quickly enough after lvl 39, but the mana requiered to kill them is a heavy burn.. downtime is too great for the piddly mob.  on the other hand we excell at npc casters such as the troll guards in rathe mountains. i have seen lvl 41 groups  yes groups camping the pair that I could solo at lvl 40 with the fire pet.  yes the fire pet.  great damage great dmg shield to distract mob from excesive casting, low hit points.. dont worry he isnt going to die, thats what your 666 double bolt is for.  a similar stategy goes for Cynthia, treants and other low HP casters that tanks fear.  Name one tank, just one that "likes" to get harm touched.  anyway im sorry i may have veered off course of the idea of the post, but there are just some tips on how to pick ur pets and pick the mobs you choose to solo.
</FONT>
