Hail all,<P>I am no high lvl mage - only 41st - but I have to add a few things maybe:<P>a) pets change at lvl 39.<P>They get an insane regen rate and heal up MUCH faster then you can medd up. You will love the fire pets from now on. The 39th pet has an damage shield of about 30 points of damage on it and casts its fire attacks.<P>==> insane regen rate - insane damage compared to the levels before<P>b) Use of pet heal:<P>I only use it a lot while in a group. When soloing I use lower nukes to add damage, because I can possibly do more damage in the time my pet can do in the time it wins when it gets back that 200 HP. At 39th I started to use pet heal again. But when I decide to use it, I use it early in fight. When pet is down to 75% I heal it. Till then I have an idea if the mob decreases the HP of my pet too fast, then I change tactic and start to nuke carefully.<P>c) Use malise a lot:<P>it helps your pet to get its spells (procs) to stick more often. I know it gets resisted a lot, but its always worth the try. I nearly never cast it twice if the first attempt was not successfull.<P>d) use when to use your diffenrent (nuke) spells:<P>I never pull with a bolt - there is a chance that it double hits and then you are on top of hate list for wuite a while. I mostly pull with malise or a weaker nuke. I use my best nuke only when monster is down to 50% HP to end the fight fast. Till then I nuke constantly but carefull with weaker nukes. Dont chain cast your nukes at the beginning. After 50% HP nuke away, if you think you can get it down quickly enough.<P>e) Which pet to use:<P>Forget about using fire pets below lvl 39 when soloing. Use them in groups only. Most wanted is here the earth pet for its root. Root gives some nice aggro, so the monsters stick at your pet. Water is nice, but cant aggro that good, therefore it has faster regen. Not worth it though. Use air pet in dunegeons - it has invisibility so it wont aggro every monster. I did not use it when soloing so far. Once you hit 39th you might want to use fire pet a lot - also when soloing. Heal is usefull then again (see above).<P>f) Get your focus items:<P>All of them. At 34th you need them. You only have to equip them while casting a new pet.<P>g) Additional help:<P>I dont have to mention that you use your best burnout spell ALL the time and equip your pet with summoned weapons (starting at 29th with runed swords, from 39th on dagger of symbols), do I? No!<P>When one of the recent patches makes norent stuff vanish on log in and not log out anymore, we got back our power of summoning good stuff. I always get a dimensional whole and fill it with daggers of symbol. If I go ld, well, np they will be still there when I get back in less then 30 mins - nearly always possible. Never used those bags before, because I was in fear of loosing the stuff that was inside.<P>h) Chain casting:<P>Forget about it in lower lvls then 39th. Eventually recasting a pet when you primary pet dies is no chain casting ;-) At higher lvls it gets interesting because its most effective manawise. Your nukes get more expensive then to cast a pet. Therefore some mages specialize in conjuration and not evocation. Helps to save even more mana.<P>But be warned, train this strategy in easy environments where you are familiar with. And carry around lots of malachite. Hehehehe ...<P>I would not cast burnout on them. You can summon one pet for two burnouts, but havent really tested this out for effectiveness.<P>Learn to find the right time to recast pet. Its just an experience thing.<P>Dont use the pet report health command (at least I dont use it), I toggle between monster and pet with F1 and F8. Much faster and more reliable.<P>Chain casting is to some degree your keyboard skill as the player and not the skill of your char.<P>Hope this helps my fellow mages. Maybe someone can add to this as I would like to learn about some strategies and tricks too.<P>Greets ... Melvyn Ghostwalker<BR>41st circle of knowledge<BR>Bristelbain Server<P>P.S.: Grab yourself an enchanter and group with him. You will love it and your pet also. ;-)
</FONT>
