<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
OH man, dont ever use the pet health bar, very inacurate, espcially if you have a garbage isp server, i have dial up so lag sucks and the pet health bar can look like it is at 75 percent and the pet report health will be 60 or 50 health, big big difference and can get you killed fast.  Get to know your enemy, knowledge is power  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> same with your pet, know how to judge the level of your pet by how hard it hits, usually you will be able to tell how long it will last depending on how hard the mob is hitting.  This is an experience thing.  Fighting blues, if your pet can solo the mob with more than half life, just blast enough to get most of the xp, then sit med and keep an eye on pet health.  This becomes safer at 35 when you dont have to look at the spell book to med.  The pet health, especially after 39, will heal itself alot faster than your mana will regen.  When fighting blues try to fight blues that will run when they get to a certain level of health, hehe as long as they dont run too fast and agro a bunch of other mobs.  Earth pet is good for keeping mobs from running, but takes extra dmg at the end of a fight when it roots.  Personally i used fire pet from 39 up, depending on what i am killling for xp i use the 51 earth or 49 fire, all depends  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  If you can get some people together you can hunt in Dalnir from 29 to 34 really fast, then move to ot to get to 39, at 39 you can solo ot all the way up to 49, hehe, i know, i did it  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
