Drew...<P>I would have to agree with many other posters above on the issue of finding nice places to solo. Personally, I think Mages are much more effective soloing in dungeons than many other classes are. Go in a dungeon, find a spot to fight from (while invis), then summon pet and go to work. a lot of Druid spells simply don't work indoors, and using fear in a dungeon isnt always the greatest of ideas, as I am sure you know  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> Try out Kedge keep from 34-39, and Kaesora after that, very nice and very easy for Mages. Also, the above poster was right on when talking about caster mobs. I have killed many a caster mob and never seen ONE spell hit me during the battle. One post I have not seen is pet weaponry being used effectively. Try spending 24-34 in South Karana. Get as many gnoll lariats as possible. KEEP THEM! DO NOT USE YET! sometimes your pets might still be a little low to get th proc effect. Once you hit 34, go to Great Divide and kill Tizmaks. Give your pet 2 gnoll lariats. I used a water pet because of my personal love of them, but any pet will work. My pet during one fight with a furious warrior had it stunned about 80% of the battle. Plus, while you are losing your gnoll lariats on pets, you are getting velium weapons to use later  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"> Hope this helps, and good luck to you.<P>--------------------<P>Cerran Cinderstorm<BR>Magician of the 39th Season<BR>Seventh Hammer Server
